msgid "Axis locking"
msgstr "軸のロック"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:15
msgid ""
":doc:`Transformations (translation/scale/rotation) "
"</3d_interaction/transformations>` in :guilabel:`Object` and "
":guilabel:`Edit` mode, as well as extrusion in :guilabel:`Edit` mode) can be"
" locked to particular axis relative to the current :doc:`transform "
"orientation </3d_interaction/transform_control/transform_orientations>`. By "
"locking a transformation to a particular axis you are restricting "
"transformations to a single dimension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:19
msgid "Usage"
msgstr "使用法"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:21
msgid ""
"A locked axis will display in a brighter color than an unlocked axis. For "
"example in the image to the right, the Z axis is drawn in light blue as "
"movement is constrained to this axis. This example can be achieved in two "
"ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:27
msgid ""
"Press :kbd:`G` to enable translation, press :kbd:`Z` to constrain movement "
"to the Z-axis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:30
msgid ""
"Press :kbd:`G` to enable translation, move the mouse in the Z direction, "
"then press :kbd:`MMB`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:34
msgid "Axis locking types"
msgstr "軸ロックタイプ"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:39
#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:55
msgid "Reference"
msgstr "リファレンス"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:46
msgid ""
"Axis locking limits the transformation to a single axis (or forbids "
"transformations along two axes). An object, face, vertex or other selectable"
" item will only be able to move, scale or rotate in a single dimension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:53
#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:66
msgid "Plane locking"
msgstr "平面のロック"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:69
msgid ""
"Plane locking locks the transformation to *two* axes (or forbids "
"transformations along one axis), thus creating a plane in which the element "
"can be moved or scaled freely. Plane locking only affects translation and "
"scaling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:74
msgid ""
"Note that for rotation, both axis and plane locking have the same effect "
"because a rotation is always constrained around one axis. "
":guilabel:`Trackball` type rotations :kbd:`R-R` cannot be locked at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:80
#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:86
msgid "Axis locking modes"
msgstr "軸ロックのモード"

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:89
msgid ""
"A single key press constrains movement to the corresponding "
":guilabel:`Global` axis. A second key press of the *same* key constrains "
"movement to the current transform orientation selection (except if it is set"
" to :guilabel:`Global`, in which case the :guilabel:`Local` orientation is "
"used). Finally, a third key press of the same key removes constraints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:95
msgid ""
"For example, if the current transform orientation is set to "
":guilabel:`Normal`, pressing :kbd:`G` to start translation, followed by "
":kbd:`Z` will lock translation in the Z direction relative to the "
":guilabel:`Global` orientation, pressing :kbd:`Z` again will lock "
"translation to the Z axis relative to the :guilabel:`Normal` orientation. "
"Pressing :kbd:`Z` again will remove all constraints. The current mode will "
"be displayed in the left hand side of the :guilabel:`3D window header`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:105
msgid ""
"As can be seen in the *Axis locking modes* image, the direction of the "
"transform also takes into account the selection. Sections A and B show Z "
"axis locking in :guilabel:`Global` and :guilabel:`Normal` orientations "
"respectively. C and D show the same situation with face selection, E and F "
"with edge selection and G and H with vertex selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/axis_locking.rst:111
msgid ""
"Note that using a locked axis does not prevent you from using the keyboard "
"to enter :doc:`numeric transformation "
"</3d_interaction/transform_control/numeric_input>` values."
msgstr ""
